snippet.title: #16DaysofActivism: CEO of Illawarra Multicultural Services, Raquel Aldunate
snippet.description:
"The obligation is on ALL our services to reach out, use interpreters, promote in community languages, and form networks and partnerships that will break down the hurdles and challenges to make a safer Australia, for ALL Australians."

CEO of Illawarra Multicultural Services, Raquel Aldunte, speaks about why it's so important for services who assist women with migrant and refugee backgrounds to be trauma, gendered violence and abuse-informed. 

We MUST implement mandatory trauma and gendered violence education and training for all health and justice qualifications, as well as specialised training for those who work with women with migrant and refugee backgrounds.

Join the national call to action here: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1fDkeoXtb54hn7QPzrxNenq-gGqJ5ROvau7QBHzvvslQ/edit#gid=0

Read the open letter here: https://www.dvnsw.org.au/wp-content/uploads/2021/11/8080-for-2031-Open-Letter-1.pdf
